# PA-GFP F153A Cavity Engineering Script
# Author: Shen Khaw
# Project: Computational Prediction of Steric Cavities in PA-GFP

# 1. Initialize and Load Structure
reinitialize
# Added ', pagfp' so the rest of the script knows what object to look at!
load T203H_baseline.pdb, pagfp

# 2. Background settings
bg_color white
set fog, off
set depth_cue, off

# 3. Basic Visualization Setup
hide everything
select chromo, resi 65-67
show sticks, chromo
color green, chromo

# 4. Engineer Novel F153A Mutation
wizard mutagenesis
alter resi 153, resn='ALA'
apply

# 5. Visualize the Cavity and Steric Environment
select f153a, resi 153
show sticks, f153a
color red, f153a

# 6. Measure Mutant Distance to Chromophore
distance mutant_dist, resi 153, chromo
# Expected result: ~13.2 Å (Expanded cavity)
# Note: PyMOL calculates all atom-to-atom distances between these residues.
# To get a single clean measurement line for the final figure:
# 1. Click the 'Measurement' wizard in the GUI.
# 2. Click the potruding part of the red residue (153).
# 3. Click the double-lined amino acid of the green chromophore (65-67).
# 4. The single distance (~13.2 Å) will appear.

# 7. Save the Final Mutated Structure
save F153A_PA-GFP_Mutant.pdb, pagfp

# 8. Render a high-quality image
ray
png F153A_chromo_distance.png, width=2000, height=2000, dpi=300
#  ^ Add folder name of where you want to save to here
